    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Neutrals & Soft Accents -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as an interactive dashboard, not a linear report. It starts with high-level KPIs for quick executive summary (The Big Picture). It then flows into deeper, interactive sections: 'Market Dynamics' for exploring growth, 'Competitive Arena' for a detailed, clickable breakdown of key players (the core interactive element), 'Industry Headwinds' for a visual summary of challenges, and 'The Next Frontier' for future trends. This structure allows users to either get a quick overview or dive deep into specific areas of interest, which is more effective for a busy audience than a long-scroll document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Market Size Forecasts -> Goal: Show Change -> Viz: Line Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover for details -> Justification: Best for showing rapid growth over time.
        - Report Info: Market Share by Component -> Goal: Compare Proportions -> Viz: Donut Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover -> Justification: Clear, simple part-to-whole comparison.
        - Report Info: Competitive Player Details (Tables 2 & 3) -> Goal: Organize & Compare -> Viz: Interactive Cards (HTML/CSS/JS) + Radar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Click player to show details & update radar chart -> Justification: Transforms static tables into an engaging, explorable deep-dive. This is the core interactive feature, allowing users to compare players on their own terms.
        - Report Info: Industry Constraints -> Goal: Inform/Organize -> Viz: Styled 3-Column Layout with Icons (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: None -> Justification: Visually breaks down complex text into scannable, thematic categories.
        - Report Info: Shift to Agentic AI -> Goal: Show Process -> Viz: Flow Diagram (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: None -> Justification: Simple visual representation of a key strategic trend without using prohibited SVG/Mermaid.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
